# Adapted from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/edt/
# `edt` uses the exact same `{?X a ?D} <= {?C rdfs:subClassOf ?D. ?X a ?C}`
# backward subClassOf rule as `deep-taxonomy` (see deep_taxonomy.n3 above),
# just over a differently-named 10000-level chain (30002 rdfs:subClassOf
# triples in test-dl.ttl) -- i.e. a scale/perf duplicate of the exact same
# feature, not a new one. Truncated here to a 3-level chain for the same
# reason deep_taxonomy.n3 is truncated: a fast conformance check rather than
# a scalability benchmark. Kept as its own case (distinct namespace/entity
# names) purely for provenance/traceability back to the separate upstream
# `edt` corpus directory, not because it exercises anything deep_taxonomy
# doesn't already cover.
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>.
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix : <http://eulersharp.sourceforge.net/2009/12dtb/edt#>.

:EdtVariable rdf:type :D0.

:D0 rdfs:subClassOf :D1.
:D1 rdfs:subClassOf :D2.
:D2 rdfs:subClassOf :B2.

{?X a ?D} <= {?C rdfs:subClassOf ?D. ?X a ?C}.
